The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Aug. 3: The government is considering a proposal to enhance foreign equity participation in captive coal mining to 100 per cent from 74 per cent at present, the Lok Sabha was informed today. In a written reply, minister of state for coal and mines Dasari Narayana Rao said according to the existing policy, foreign equity up to 100 per cent have been allowed in private Indian companies setting up or operating power projects and coal or lignite mines provided they use it for captive consumption. 

 New Delhi, Aug. 3: The open offer by Oracle to acquire 20 per cent of the shares in i-flex Software Solutions will start on September 27. Oracle will pay Rs 882.6 per share for acquiring 15,586,914 shares from the open market. The last date for the open offer is October 17.

 Beijing, Aug. 3: Infosys Technologies (Shanghai) Company Ltd will invest $10 million to build a state-of-the-art software campus in Shanghai. 

 Mumbai, Aug 3: The First Global group has called off its acquisition of Way2wealth Securities Ltd, a financial services company in the retail space, for non-compliance with certain clauses in pact by sellers.

 New Delhi, Aug. 3: Orchid Chemicals amp; Pharmaceuticals Ltd has received formal approval from USFDA for its generic ceftriaxone abbreviated new drug application.




